# GitHub Pages Setup

This repository is configured to use GitHub Pages for documentation.

## Setup Instructions

1. Enable GitHub Pages in repository settings
2. Select source branch: `master` or `main`
3. Select source folder: `/docs`
4. Save settings

## Documentation Structure

```
docs/
├── index.html       # Main documentation page
├── README.md        # Documentation overview
└── gitpages        # GitHub Pages configuration
```

## Deployment

Documentation is automatically deployed when changes are pushed to the main branch.

## Access

Once deployed, documentation will be available at:
```
https://<username>.github.io/<repository-name>/
```

## Notes

- The `/docs` folder contains static HTML files for GitHub Pages
- Ensure all links and resources use relative paths
- Test locally before pushing changes
